n-yellow-shirt-with-farmers--1740633577-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F02%2FKarekar-in-yellow-shirt-with-farmers--1740633577-500x281.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F02%2FKarekar-in-yellow-shirt-with-farmers--1740633577-150x84.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-410064%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22405%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ESachin%20Kamlakar%20Karekar%20and%20other%20turmeric%20farmers%20discuss%20the%20SK-4%20variety%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElaborating%20on%20the%20agronomic%20practices%20for%20cultivating%20the%20SK-4%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20rhizomes%20or%20fingers%20are%20planted%20in%20nursery%20bags%20in%20April%2C%20and%20by%20June%20they%20are%20transplanted%20on%20fields%20prepared%20with%20organic%20fertiliser.%20In%20August%2C%20the%20saplings%20are%20fed%20a%20second%20dose%20of%20water-soluble%20fertiliser.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20crop%20is%20irrigated%20till%20January%20and%20harvested%20in%20the%20last%20week%20of%20February%2C%20with%20each%20sapling%20yielding%203.2%20kg%20or%20more.%20He%20has%20been%20propagating%20the%20variety%20for%20ten%20years%20now%20and%20regularly%20imparts%C2%A0training%20on%20plantation%20management%20to%20farmers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGrowing%20the%20rhizomes%20in%20nursery%20bags%20rather%20than%20planting%20them%20directly%20on%20the%20field%20offers%2090%20per%20cent%20success%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20farmer%20Gajendra%20Paunikar%20(55)%20of%20Nigundan%20village%2C%20who%20was%2C%20till%20very%20recently%2C%20the%20Agriculture%20Extension%20Officer%2C%20Panchayat%20Samiti%2C%20Guhagar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%224678180483%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-artic